Library.description: This soa library contains SOA operations required for Electronic Work Instruction project.
Library.name: Ewi0SoaEwia

ParameterInfo.description: The input object for the report generation SOA.

Operation.description: Generates printable report for the EWI.
Operation.name: generatePrintableReport

ParameterInfo.description: the vector of cortona files for which read ticket is required.

Operation.description: Returns the file read ticket of the Cortona 3D animation (.wrl) file from the given Cortona build file.
Operation.name: getCortonaAnimationFileTicket
Operation.returnDescription: The file read ticket of animation file.

Operation.description: This operation returns the given relation/property data of input business objects. For every relation/property, you can specify the type of required objects you want to load. In case you want to load all of the objects related, then pass empty list of types.
Operation.name: getRelated
Operation.returnDescription: The relations/properties data by given types.

Operation.description: Load required work package data for Ewi.
Operation.name: loadWorkPackageData
Operation.returnDescription: Required work package data for Ewi.

ParameterInfo.description: A vector containing the input structures.

Operation.description: This operation loads work package data with optional configuration parameters to the EWI (Electronic Work Instructions) application. Work package is a Collaboration Context object packaging manufacturing structures with specific configuration settings. The additionl configuration parameters can be used to apply further , on-demand, configuration settings on top of the work package configuration.
Operation.name: loadWorkPackageDataConfigured
Operation.returnDescription:
The requested work package data.
The following partial errors may be returned:
    • 115001 - The operation "loadWorkPackageData" has failed because the input does not contain work package information. Please contact your system administrator.
    • 115002 - The creation of an Electronic Work Instruction object for the work package has failed. Please contact your system administrator.
    • 115003 - The creation of an Electronic Work Instruction object for the current step has failed. Please contact your system administrator.
    • 115004 - None of the preferred navigation structures are found in the selected work package. Either add a value to the preference "EWI_NavigationStructure" (in order to open a different navigation structure), or select a different work package.
    • 115007 - Teamcenter Electronic Work Instructions (EWI) license is not installed. Please contact your system administrator.
